data.title: Nomad Foods prices term loans totaling USD 620 million and EUR 880 million, with SOFR rate plus 2.5% interest, due 2032.
data.description: A company based in Woking, England, Nomad Foods Limited, has revealed that they have set the prices for two term loans. The first loan is USD 620 million, with an annual interest rate of the SOFR rate plus 2.5%, scheduled to be paid off by 2032. The second loan amounts to EUR 880 million.

data.title: Univers launches World-First Global Impact AI Lab with AMD, Microsoft, NUS to accelerate enterprise AI and IoT, on Oct 30, 2025, in Singapore.
data.description: Singapore-based Univers, a renowned AI company specializing in energy solutions, has revealed the establishment of the pioneering Global Impact AI Lab (IAL). This initiative, carried out in partnership with AMD, Microsoft, and the National University of Singapore (NUS), has garnered support from the Infocomm Media Development. The lab is set to make waves as the first of its kind globally, signaling a significant milestone in the field.

data.title: L3Harris Technologies Q3 2025: Orders $6.7B; Revenue $5.7B, up 7%. Operating margin 11.0%. Diluted EPS $2.46. Guidance increased.
data.description: In the third quarter of 2025, L3Harris Technologies (NYSE: LHX) based in Melbourne, Florida, released their financial results. They reported receiving orders totaling $6.7 billion with a book-to-bill ratio of 1.2x. Revenue for the quarter was $5.7 billion, showing a 7% increase from the previous year, with a 10% increase organically. They achieved an operating margin of 11.0% and an adjusted segment operating margin of 15.9%. Diluted earnings per share (EPS) were $2.46, while non-GAAP diluted EPS stood at $2.70, reflecting a 10% increase compared to the previous year. Following their strong performance and heightened expectations, L3Harris Technologies raised their guidance for the year 2025. The company expressed satisfaction with their strong quarterly performance.

data.title: Eagle Pharmaceuticals extends limited duration stockholder rights plan to Oct 30, 2026.(board of directors made the decision)
data.description: In Woodcliff Lake, New Jersey, on October 30, 2025, Eagle Pharmaceuticals, Inc. (OTCMKTS: EGRX) disclosed that its Board of Directors has approved an extension of the existing limited duration stockholder rights plan (now amended as the "Rights Plan") by one year. The amendment sets the plan duration until October 30, 2026, and is now in effect.

data.title: Timken to join Baird Global Industrial Conference on Nov. 11, 2025 in Chicago; a global leader in engineered bearings.
data.description: On October 30, 2025, The Timken Company, a prominent player in engineered bearings and industrial motion technologies, announced its participation in the Baird Global Industrial Conference in Chicago, Illinois on November 11, 2025. Timken, listed on NYSE as TKR and known for its innovative solutions, will be showcasing its advancements to a wide audience at the conference. This event, scheduled for the upcoming Tuesday, is a strategic opportunity for Timken to highlight its expertise and offerings in the industrial sector.

data.title: Cleveland-Cliffs Inc. priced public offering of 75M Common Shares. Expected gross proceeds $964M, plus option for 11.25M more shares. Offer closes on Oct 31, 2025.
data.description: Cleveland-based company Cleveland-Cliffs Inc. (NYSE: CLF) disclosed details of its recent underwritten public offering, announcing the pricing of 75,000,000 common shares at a par value of $0.125 per share. The offering is expected to generate around $964 million in gross proceeds, excluding discounts and expenses. Additionally, an option has been granted to the underwriter to procure an extra 11,250,000 Common Shares within a 30-day period. The closing of this offering is slated for October 31, 2025.

data.title: Hershey's Q3 2025 financial results exceed expectations with strong net sales and earnings; updates 2025 outlook.
data.description: Hershey, Pennsylvania, October 30, 2025 - The Hershey Company (HSY) disclosed their net sales and earnings for the third quarter ending on September 28, 2025. They also provided an updated 2025 outlook range. The company exceeded expectations in the third quarter due to robust innovation and strategic brand initiatives.
